weather along with the steps to safely resolve the issue and protect your garage door.";i:14;s:30:"Check Your Garage Door Opener.";i:15;s:145:"If your garage door is not working properly and you have an automatic garage door opener disconnect the opener and try to open the door manually.";i:16;s:58:"If the door opens fine the issue could be related to your.";i:17;s:30:"Ive got the same problem here.";i:18;s:88:"When it gets cold I need to hold the button on the wall to get the garage door to close.";i:19;s:47:"Remotes dont work for closing only for opening.";i:20;s:115:"Ive checked the door manually and it moves up and down fine and the sensor is clear and appears to be working fine.";i:21;s:41:"My unit is a Stanley chain driven opener.";i:22;s:74:"Disconnect the garage door from the opener and manually open and close it.";i:23;s:98:"If it opens and closes without great difficulty this rules out track and garage door panel issues.";i:24;s:37:"Garage doors operate in cold weather.";i:25;s:58:"Its -30F where I live and everyone here has a garage door.";i:26;s:104:"During cold weather door will not close unless you hold the button on wall in during the entire process.";i:27;s:21:"Remote will not work.";i:28;s:69:"It activates but just flashes the light and returns to open position.";i:29;s:39:"Garage door wont close in cold weather.";i:30;s:57:"My garage door works perfectly when its above 45 degrees.";i:31;s:115:"As it gets colder I have to hold the wall mounted master garage door openercloser in to have the garage door close.";i:32;s:20:"Ive lubed the rails.";i:33;s:43:"Common Cold Weather Garage Door Problems 1.";i:34;s:34:"Malfunctioning Garage Door Opener.";i:35;s:123:"The opener is that small electrically powered box-like device at the top of the door that controls its opening and closing.";i:36;s:104:"Cold temperatures can hinder the performance of the openers motor and other essential system components.";i:37;s:77:"Troubleshooting a Garage That Wont Close in Cold Weather Check the Batteries.";i:38;s:99:"Extremely cold temperatures can wreak havoc on batteries and garage door remotes depend on them to.";i:39;s:29:"Disengage the Lift Mechanism.";i:40;s:84:"Disengaging the garage door from its lift mechanism will allow you to open the door.";i:41;s:163:"It sounds to me like what might be happening is as the door tries to come up its getting stuck because when the temperature drops like that the lubricants dry out.";i:42;s:196:"You can get some moisture in the hinges and it seizes and it might be that the safety reverse mechanism on this opener is basically thinking that something is stuck and so its shutting itself off.";i:43;s:59:"For this reason the garage door wont close when it is cold.";i:44;s:70:"Applying lubrication can reduce the contraction of the metallic parts.";i:45;s:33:"Frozen grease or lubricating oil.";i:46;s:101:"If the garage door opener is not working in cold weather it could be because the grease has hardened.";i:47;s:78:"It is only natural for grease for lubricating oils to freeze up during winter.";i:48;s:72:"If you notice little to no light at all it is time to get a new emitter.";i:49;s:80:"If this is the only problem your garage door will open and close with no issues.";i:50;s:67:"It is no brainer that metal contracts when exposed to cold weather.";i:51;s:98:"While contracting garage door experts say the door sensors will shift from their normal positions.";i:52;s:101:"You can try all you can but the door cannot tell if there is an obstruction when the sensors are not.";i:53;s:94:"The most common cause for your door not closing in the morning but will close at night is the.";i:54;s:68:"These sensors prevent the door from closing if the sensor beam gets.";i:55;s:83:"This safety feature is required on garage doors and keeps the door from closing on.";i:56;s:73:"In NapervilleIL the Garage Door Wont Close cold weather issues - YouTube.";i:57;s:83:"Cold weather can drain batteries in garage door opener re